            <!-- Section 1: Fortress -->
            <section class="content-section">
<h3 class="subsection-heading">Architectural Security</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>SafeKeepVault</strong> Starts up secure and ready to use. Every boot is a fresh, clean slate—no setup needed, no lingering data, and no hidden risks. It’s designed to be safe by default, every single time.
                </p>

                <h3 class="subsection-heading">Absolute Air-Gap</h3>
                <ul class="spec-list">
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Total Network Isolation</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc"><strong>SafeKeepVault</strong> locks down Ethernet, Wi-Fi, and access to the host's storage before the system even fully starts. This ensures your private keys are completely isolated and never even have the chance to see the internet or the local drive.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Hardware Lockdown</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc">Non-essential peripherals, including microphones and speakers, are deactivated. The system communicates exclusively with your display, keyboard, camera, and the USB drive itself.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subsection-heading">Zero-Footprint Operations</h3>
                <ul class="spec-list">
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Host Integrity</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc"><strong>SafeKeepVault</strong> operates in complete isolation from your computer's internal storage. Your hard drive is never mounted, read, or modified, ensuring your host OS remains untouched.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Volatile Memory Execution</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc">By running entirely in RAM, all session data&mdash;including keys and clipboard history&mdash;is instantly purged upon shutdown. No traces are ever written to the local hardware.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subsection-heading">Temporary or Encrypted Versatility</h3>
                <ul class="spec-list">
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Persistent or Stateless</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc">Choose your workflow for every session. Utilize the Encrypted Vault to securely store keys for recurring use, or run Stateless for using a different private key or multi-signature setup.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Streamlined Authentication</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc">Access your encrypted storage securely and conveniently. Authenticate by scanning a secure QR code via your mobile device or through traditional password entry.</span>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="spec-label">Plausible Deniability</span>
                        <span class="spec-desc">Transform any standard PC into a signing station without specialized, branded hardware. To an outside observer, your vault is an indistinguishable, everyday USB drive.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

